法規內容.條文內容:
Whoever has any one condition of the followings shall not practice as a social worker ; if he has practiced, his certificate of social worker shall be withdrew or abolished：
1. his social worker certification has been abolished under this Act;
2. he has been confirmed as insanity or disorder in physical or mental by related medical specialist physician commissioned by the competent authority and can not perform his duty; 
3. he has been placed under supervision or consultation and such supervision or consultation has not yet been revoked;
4. he has been convicted of the crimes of embezzlement, domestic violence, sexual harassment, forced sex acts;
5. other than those prescribed in the preceding subparagraph, having been convicted of any intentional criminal acts related to the profession.　Once the causes prescribed in preceding subparagraphs 2 and 3 ceases to exist he or she may still apply for social worker certification under this Act.

Whoever has any one condition of the followings shall not be granted for business license; if he has obtained it, the business license shall be withdrew or rescinded：
1. his social worker certification has been rescinded under this Act;
2. his social worker business license has been rescinded for less than one year;
3. he has been confirmed as insanity or disorder in physical or mental by related medical specialist physician commissioned by the competent authority and can not perform his duty;　
4. he has been placed under supervision or consultation and such supervision or consultation has not yet been revoked;
5. he has been convicted of the crimes of embezzlement, domestic violence, sexual harassment, forced sex acts;
6. other than those prescribed in the preceding subparagraph, having been convicted of any intentional criminal acts related to the profession.　Once the causes prescribed in preceding subparagraphs 3 and 4 ceases to exist he or she may still apply for the business license under this Act.

A social worker shall engage in the following business:
1. social and psychological evaluation and disposition of the problems about behavior, social relationship, marriage, social adaptation and so on;
2. protective services prescribed in each relevant social welfare act; 
3. prevent and support services for an individual, a family, an organization and a community;
4. development, conformity, exertion, distribution, and transfer of social welfare service resources; 
5. Design, manage, study, develop, guide, appraise, educate, train, etc. social service programs as it relates to social service agencies and groups or disease control, employment, education, law enforcement, national defense fields. design, management, research and development, supervision, evaluation and training of social welfare projects implemented by social welfare organization or projects or in the fields of health, job-placement, education, justice and national security; 
6. maintenance of the people’s social welfare rights;
7. any other business which has been confirmed by the central competent authority or together with target enterprise competent authority.

The advertisement content of social worker office shall be limited in the following items:
1. the appellation, opening license character and number, address, telephone number and transportation lines of social worker office; 
2. the name, certificate character and number of social worker;
3. the business of social work prescribed in Article 12;
4. any other item permitted to issue or advertise and announced by the central competent authority. 
Any one except social worker office shall not issue advertisement prescribed in the preceding paragraph.
